# üìê CIDR & Subnetting in AWS

## CIDR (Classless Inter-Domain Routing)

CIDR notation defines IP ranges using the format: `IP/Prefix`
Example: `10.0.0.0/16`

- `/16` = 65,536 IPs
- `/24` = 256 IPs
- `/28` = 16 IPs (13 usable)

## Subnetting

Subnetting splits a VPC CIDR into smaller blocks.

Example:
- VPC: `10.0.0.0/16`
- Subnet A: `10.0.1.0/24` (Public)
- Subnet B: `10.0.2.0/24` (Private)

## Practice

| CIDR         | Total IPs | Usable IPs | 
|--------------|-----------|------------|
| 10.0.0.0/24  | 256       | 251        |
| 10.0.0.0/28  | 16        | 11         |
